Durban — Ever wondered why when you turn over your vehicle’s key, the radio momentarily powers down or your dash lights dim? That is a pointer that your battery has outlived its time and needs to be replaced. There are things that lead to the downfall of your battery, one being a faulty alternator, as it causes battery power loss. Another issue is corrosion on the battery, which is a white or blue flaky build-up on the terminals. Battery Centre is offering a brand new long-lasting Raylite battery worth R2 500 that is suitable for a vehicle or a motorcycle. One lucky reader stands a chance to win a R2 500 voucher from Battery Centre. To enter, SMS DNBATTERY your name and surname to 33258. SMSes cost R1.50. Terms and conditions apply. The competition closes on Friday, July 1, at 8am. Daily News